{"title_page": "Louis Okoye", "text_new": "{{Infobox NPB player\n| name        = Louis Okoye\n| image       = Rakuten okoye9.JPG\n| image_size  = 250px\n| caption     = Okoye in 2016\n| position    = [[Outfielder]]\n| team        = Tohoku Rakuten Golden Eagles\n| number      = 4\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1997|7|21}}\n| bats        = Right\n| throws      = Right\n| debutleague = [[Nippon Professional Baseball|NPB]]\n| debutdate   = March 25\n| debutyear   = 2016\n| debutteam   = [[Tohoku Rakuten Golden Eagles]]\n| statyear    = 2019 season\n| statleague  = NPB\n| stat1label  = [[Batting average (baseball)|Batting average]]\n| stat1value  = .219\n| stat2label  = [[Home run]]s\n| stat2value  = 9\n| stat3label  = [[Run batted in|Runs batted in]]\n| stat3value  = 38\n| teams       =\n*[[Tohoku Rakuten Golden Eagles]] ({{baseball year|2016}}&ndash;present)\n| highlights  =\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Louis Okoye'''|\u30aa\u30b3\u30a8 \u7460\u5049|Okoe Rui|born July 21, 1997 in [[Higashimurayama, Tokyo]]}} is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] professional [[baseball]] [[outfielder]] for the [[Tohoku Rakuten Golden Eagles]] in [[Japan]]'s [[Nippon Professional Baseball]].\n\nAfter the 2017 season, he joined [[Ca\u00f1eros de Los Mochis]].<ref>{{cite web |first1= |last1= |url=https://www.lmp.mx/noticia/16517  |title=CA\u00d1EROS ADQUIEREN AL OF JAPONES LOUIS OKOYE |work=Sitio Oficial de la Liga Mexicana del Pac\u00edfico |language=Spanish |date=November 24, 2017 |accessdate=January 13, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nOkoye's mother is Japanese and his father is [[Igbo people|Igbo]].<ref>{{cite AV media |date=January 20, 2017 |title=Meet Nigerian baseball star who can't speak English, local dialect |medium= |language= |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P_gt_-acxsc |access-date=March 31, 2019 |publisher=Oak TV }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Baseballstats|brm=okoye-000lou}}\n*[http://npb.jp/bis/eng/players/01505132.html NPB stats]\n\n{{Tohoku Rakuten Golden 